text: Katharine Helen Brooks-Osborne is a British Labour Party politician. She has been the Member of Parliament (MP) for Jarrow since the 2019 general election. Osborne is known for being a trade union and a LGBT+ activist and campaigner. Osborne is married to Pamela Brooks-Osborn. In March 2020, Osborne became the second British Member of Parliament to test positive for Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19), after Nadine Dorries. ==References== Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people) Category:Labour Party (UK) MPs Category:UK MPs 2019â€“2024 Category:Lesbians Category:British LGBT politicians
